====Good Morning, Sunshine====
{{Image Banner|image=Foggy_Skyscrapers_Daytime_IMG.jpg|caption=You should have enjoyed it.}}
===You should have enjoyed all these===
The sun rose.

Again, the glorious sunshine, illuminating the land, the city, the advancement.

A warm sensation could be felt. It is light, it is comfy. It is the cycle of the land you stand on.

This is always cycling as if it is eternal. The eternal sunshine. The city, waking up from fogginess. 

The lights are off one by one, revealing the true colors of skyscrapers. Without saturated color masking around them endlessly. This moment is yours, my dear friend. What a wonderful morning. No hustle, only silence.

This is the beginning, the starting point, the road that you are continuously walking. It all starts from cycles like this.

We missed, we overlooked, we walked past. Immersing ourselves in the glamour of lights and dazzling shininess.

If you have another chance to choose again, to feel.

If and only if you will have the chance to choose again. Will you stop by, stare at the moment before thriving for just a second?

But will you?

===Another Day of Norm===
You woke up from your bed.

Your windows are closed, curtains masking all the sunlight.

You woke up, switched on the lights, pulled a chair and sat in front of a computer. Typing.

The sun turns from brilliant, slowly from golden to orange, sinking from top to bottom.

Before you even noticed, it is the end of a day.

But... is it really what happened?

8:20 am, you woke up.

8:20 am, your neighbor opened her door with a flowery pattern, holding a shopping bag. She is going to shop in the store again.

8:25 am, a car crash happened in the city, beneath the skyscrapers outside your window.

8:25 am, you switched on your computer. You think you are connected to the world.

8:30 am, a beam of sunshine slipped into your house, giving your flower a moment of joy.

8:35 am, cars passed by. Sunshine is reflected by the car surfaces, giving them a golden mask.

8:40 am, humans walked out of their homes, preparing for a new day of work.

8:45 am, you started your first game. 

You lost your sensation.

===A Morning Tale===

If the world will give you another chance, do not ever lose your sensation for the colorful world.

There was once a woman who had a child.

The child grew up day after day, fed and nurtured under great care.

Remember his or her first day of school.

Remember his or her first time growing a plant, laughing with dirt on his or her cute face.

Remember his or her first time giving a present to his or her mother.

Remember his or her 18th birthday.

Time will wash away memories. One day, the sunshine was no longer shiny in his or her eyes. 

The mother, standing alone in the kitchen, sunshine gave her a golden coat. It could be the responsibility, or the care, or everything she gave this family.

Her back looked very small.

Then, the child, no longer willing to see the sunshine again.

Soon afterwards, everything declined.

The child met more people, learned more.

But the sunshine was not as shiny as before. Its color got paler and paler.

One day, the sunshine could not shine anymore. It could be her last day.

You met her on the last day. Then, darkness arrived.
{{Blurimage|file=br_skyscraperlightending.webp|caption=The story is never a city tale, but a tale in your heart.}}
You saw glorious and glistening neon, vivid lights on skyscrapers. You have your own area to explore.

It was the end of sunshine. You have never seen it since then.

If I have the chance to see the sunshine again in the morning...

Good morning, my dearest sunshine.

When you walk under sunshine again,

what you are carrying, is another perspective towards the world.

